# Goal

Build a premium, responsive, bilingual (English + Telugu) website for S. Mallareddy, Sarpanch of Narsimhunipeta Village. The website will highlight development works, welfare activities, and provide contact/grievance mechanisms. The key focus is on a premium look (Refined Minimalism), high performance on slow networks, and avoiding heavy JavaScript libraries.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - I will be using **Vite with Vanilla HTML/JS/CSS**. This ensures no heavy framework (like React or Next.js) is shipped to the user, strictly adhering to your requirement of "Minimal JS" and "Fast load on slow networks" while still giving us a modern build tool to compress assets.
> - For bilingual support, I will implement a custom, lightweight vanilla JS function that swaps text based on a `translations.json` dictionary.
> - I will generate high-quality placeholder images for the Hero, Development Works, and Gallery sections to ensure the design looks complete and premium.

