## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup
- **Initialize Vite**: Run `npx create-vite` to set up a vanilla web project in `c:\projects`.

### Core Application
- **`index.html`**: The single-page application structure. Will contain:
  - Sticky Header with navigation and language toggle.
  - Hero Section (Text + Image).
  - Trust/Impact Stats (Numbers & Icons).
  - Development Works Grid.
  - Welfare Activities.
  - Gallery (with simple lightweight vanilla lightbox).
  - Contact & Grievance Forms.
  - Floating WhatsApp Button.

- **`style.css`**:
  - CSS Variables for the color system (Primary: #2E7D32, Background: #FFFFFF, etc.).
  - Typography setup importing `Inter` and `Noto Sans Telugu` from Google Fonts.
  - Responsive layouts (Mobile-first, Flexbox/Grid).
  - Subtle micro-interactions (hover scales, light shadows).

- **`src/main.js`**:
  - Sticky header scroll effect.
  - Mobile menu toggle.
  - Lightweight scroll-into-view animations (using `IntersectionObserver`).
  - Lightbox logic for the gallery.

- **`src/i18n.js` & `src/translations.js`**:
  - A small script that stores the English and Telugu text strings.
  - Replaces text in elements marked with `data-i18n` attributes when the language toggle is clicked.
  - Updates the body font family when switching to Telugu.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to verify that Vite bundles successfully without errors.
- Ensure the bundle size is extremely small (target < 100KB JS).

### Manual Verification
- Use the built-in browser subagent to open the development server.
- Verify the sticky header, smooth scrolling, and translations toggle.
- Check mobile layout responsiveness.
- Verify aesthetic quality against the "Premium but clean" requirement.
